I"¯<p>V-Ray for Rhino is a photorealistic rendering software. Students at the School of Architecture are free to use SoA network licenses via the VPN.</p>

<p><strong>Installation Instructions</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Make sure <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1wCTRnF4LN5J2-UyHIXnTLYNrmbe7Sohl?usp=sharing">Rhino is installed</a> and functional.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Close all instances of Rhino.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Open the V-ray Installer.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The End User License Agreement opens, click <em>I Agree</em></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>You will now be taken to the Installation parameters page. Leave The Rhinoceros 6 box checked and un-check <em>V-ray Swarm</em>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The next step is Licensing Setup. Un-Check <em>License Server 5.1.1</em>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Select <em>Remote V-ray license server on the network</em>. Once selected, additional options will appear.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Under Primary License Server enter in: <em>128.2.24.236</em>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>For Alternate License Server 1 enter: <em>flexserv19</em>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Leave all other settings at default.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Select <em>Install Now</em>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Under the Finished section, Un-Check ‚ÄúHelp us improve V-ray for Rhinoceros 6‚Äù and select ‚ÄúFinish‚Äù.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<hr />

<p><strong>Remember:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Licenses are limited to 110 simultaneous instances.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Close Vray when you don‚Äôt need it so that others may use it!</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Alternatively, <a href="https://store.chaosgroup.com/product/edu-vray-rhino-student">$99 (1-year) student license can be purchased</a>.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

